00:14:10.980 --> 00:14:13.940
And here's radius or
mass-- two graphs here.

00:14:13.940 --> 00:14:15.960
And again, we favor
a lot of mass.

00:14:15.960 --> 00:14:19.034
So it's complete out
here in these regions.

00:14:19.034 --> 00:14:21.450
But down in this corner here,
that's the hard place to be.

00:14:21.450 --> 00:14:22.580
And this is where we live.

00:14:22.580 --> 00:14:27.950
We live right here, one radius
and 365 and a quarter days,

00:14:27.950 --> 00:14:29.860
except we make a correction
every four years.

00:14:29.860 --> 00:14:31.100
That's the four days.

00:14:31.100 --> 00:14:34.540
We make a correction every
100 years, or 300s out of 400.

00:14:34.540 --> 00:14:35.850
You know about that stuff?

00:14:35.850 --> 00:14:38.230
Most people don't live long
enough to care about it.

00:14:38.230 --> 00:14:39.420
Astronomers worry
about it, because we've

00:14:39.420 --> 00:14:41.128
got to keep track
going all the way back.

00:14:41.128 --> 00:14:43.140
Anyway, this is the
impossible place to go,

00:14:43.140 --> 00:14:44.750
but we can try to
extrapolate and see

00:14:44.750 --> 00:14:48.680
what you can do with this,
and people have done that.

00:14:48.680 --> 00:14:51.650
The ones that are hardest
to see, we've tried hard.

