00:55:27.670 --> 00:55:30.600
Notice we use nonlinear
levels, because you

00:55:30.600 --> 00:55:32.930
can do that if you set
your own drip points.

00:55:32.930 --> 00:55:35.660
And the jiggly red
line is ground truth,

00:55:35.660 --> 00:55:37.760
with a gigahertz scope.

00:55:37.760 --> 00:55:42.930
And the black line is what this
crazy kluged up ADC measures

00:55:42.930 --> 00:55:43.780
for a double pulse.

00:55:43.780 --> 00:55:44.660
So it works great.

00:55:44.660 --> 00:55:45.451
Thing really works.

